{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e562fe5b-85d7-4d70-bfe5-7af9a2348f31","content":"In .NET MAUI, `Application.OnStart()`, `OnSleep()`, and `OnResume()` **still exist** — you can override them the same way. However, MAUI also adds a more granular lifecycle API on the **`Window`** class:\n\n| Xamarin.Forms | MAUI Window equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `OnStart()` | `OnCreated()` |\n| `OnSleep()` | `OnDeactivated()` / `OnStopped()` |\n| `OnResume()` | `OnResumed()` / `OnActivated()` |\n\nYou can override these on a custom `Window`, or use the fluent `ILifecycleBuilder` API in `CreateMauiApp()`:\n\n```csharp\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnStart((activity) => Log.Debug(\"App\", \"Started\"))\n        .OnStop((activity) => Log.Debug(\"App\", \"Stopped\")));\n#elif IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .OnActivated((app) => Log.Debug(\"App\", \"Activated\")));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**TL;DR:** Your existing overrides will compile and work. For finer control (per-platform or per-window), use the `Window` lifecycle overrides or `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fa2d9d1e-90dc-4601-af83-f24b5bc988df","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating lifecycle methods from Xamarin.Forms to .NET MAUI. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.\n\nIn Xamarin.Forms, you'd override `OnStart()`, `OnSleep()`, and `OnResume()` in your `Application` subclass.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the same three virtual methods still exist on `Microsoft.Maui.Controls.Application`, so you can still override them. However, MAUI also introduces a more granular, cross-platform lifecycle API via the `Window` class and `ILifecycleBuilder`.\n\nLet me give a concise answer.","outputTokens":506,"requestId":"0433:1DE8C5:D0D573:EBF707:6A027A80"},"id":"b2061591-a22e-4ea2-8118-27e357493ba0","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:55:39.277Z","parentId":"76b44222-e80c-4175-8873-a069eca5c172"}
